## Code of Conduct

By participating in this project you agree to abide by our [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). Please read it before contributing.

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone {{ homepage | default(value="https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/" ~ repoName) }}
cd {{ repoName }}
```

{% if primaryLanguage %}
- Ensure you have **{{ primaryLanguage }}** installed and up to date.
{% endif %}

### Fork and Branch

1. [Fork]({{ homepage | default(value="https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/" ~ repoName) }}/fork) the repository.
2. Create a feature branch from `main`:

```bash
git checkout -b feat/your-feature-name
```

3. Keep your fork in sync with upstream:

```bash
git remote add upstream {{ homepage | default(value="https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/" ~ repoName) }}
git fetch upstream
git rebase upstream/main
```

---

## How to Contribute

### Bug Fixes

- Open an issue describing the bug before submitting a fix.
- Reference the issue number in your pull request (`Fixes #123`).

### New Features

- Open a discussion or issue to propose the feature first.
- Small, focused pull requests are preferred over large sweeping changes.

### Documentation

- Documentation improvements are always welcome.
- Keep examples accurate and runnable.

---

## Development Workflow

```bash
# Install dependencies and build
# (see README.md for language-specific instructions)

# Run the test suite
just test

# Check formatting and linting
just lint

# Verify the build
just check
```

All pull requests must pass the full test suite and linter before review.

---

## Pull Request Process

1. Ensure your branch is up to date with `main`.
2. Write or update tests for your changes.
3. Run `just pre-commit` (or the project equivalent) locally.
4. Open a pull request with a clear title and description.
5. Reference any related issues using GitHub keywords (`Closes #N`, `Fixes #N`).
6. A maintainer will review your pull request within **5 business days**.
7. Address feedback promptly; stale PRs may be closed after 30 days of inactivity.

### Commit Messages

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
feat(scope): add new widget renderer
fix(scope): handle nil pointer in parser
docs(scope): update installation steps
```

---

## Reporting Bugs

Please file bugs via [GitHub Issues]({{ homepage | default(value="https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/" ~ repoName) }}/issues) and include:

- A clear, descriptive title.
- Steps to reproduce the problem.
- Expected vs. actual behaviour.
- Environment details (OS, {% if primaryLanguage %}{{ primaryLanguage }} version, {% endif %}relevant dependency versions).

---

## Suggesting Enhancements

Feature requests are welcome. Open an issue with the label `enhancement` and describe:

- The problem you are trying to solve.
- Your proposed solution.
- Alternatives you have considered.

